         MACRO
         AFIOEQU
*
* REGISTER DEFINITIONS FOR ACTIVE FILE I/O ACCESS MODULES.
*
SAVERG  EQU  7
KBXRG  EQU  8
LBXRG  EQU  12
BASERG  EQU  10
FBXRG  EQU  12
*
* PRIMARY RAFIO REGISTER DEFINITIONS
*
GR0RG    EQU   0 .                WORK REGISTERS
GR1RG    EQU   1 .
GR2RG    EQU   2 .
GR3RG    EQU   3 .
INTLNKRG EQU   4 .                LOWEST LEVEL LINKAGE AND WORK
CCWRG    EQU   5 .                CCW LIST BASE
SRCHRG   EQU   6 .                SEARCH ARGUMENT LIST BASE
ICRG     EQU   SAVERG .           INSERT CHARACTER REGISTER
AFWRG    EQU   9
LINK1RG  EQU   14 .               PRIMARY LINKAGE REGISTER
LINK2RG  EQU   15 .               SECONDARY LINKAGE REGISTER
*
* SECONDARY RAFIO REGISTER DEFINITIONS
*
AFPARG   EQU   GR0RG .            USER PARAMENTER REGISTER
GRERG    EQU   GR0RG .            EVEN REGISTER
GRORG    EQU   GR1RG .            ODD REGISTER
GRDRG    EQU   GR2RG .            DIVISOR WORK REGISTER
GRD2RG   EQU   GR3RG .            SECOND DIVIDE REGISTER
INCRG    EQU   GR1RG .            INCREMENT AND MASK REG. FOR ALLOCATOR
CYLERG   EQU   GR2RG .            EVEN REGISTER FOR TRACK ALLOCATION
CYLORG   EQU   GR3RG .             ODD REGISTER FOR TRACK ALLOCATION
HEADRG   EQU   INTLNKRG .         WORK REGISTER FOR ALLOCATOR
*
* REGISTER DEFINITIONS FOR APPENDAGES.
*
APIOBRG  EQU   2 .                POINTER TO IOB
APW1RG   EQU   10 .               APPENDAGE WORK REG. CCW POINTER
APW2RG   EQU   11 .               KONBOX POINTER
APW3RG   EQU   12 .               LINE BOX POINTER
APRETRG  EQU   14 .               APPENDAGE RETURN REGISTER
APBASERG EQU   15 .               PROGRAM BASE REGISTER
*
* CCW FLAG BITS.
*
CD       EQU   B'10000000' .      CHAIN DATA
CC       EQU   B'01000000' .      CHAIN COMMAND
SILI     EQU   B'00100000' .      SUPPRESS INCORRECT LENGTH INDICATOR
SKIP     EQU   B'00010000' .      SUPPRESS TRANSFER OF INFORMATION
PCI      EQU   B'00001000' .      PROGRAM CONTROLLED INTERRUPT
*
* CCW COMMAND CODES.
*
READHA   EQU   26 .               READ HOME ADDRESS
READCKD  EQU   30 .               READ COUNT-KEY-DATA
READKD   EQU   14 .               READ KEY-DATA
READD    EQU   6 .                READ DATA
WRITECKD EQU   29 .               WRITE COUNT-KEY-DATA
WRITEKD  EQU   13 .               WRITE KEY-DATA
WRITED   EQU   5 .                WRITE DATA
SRCHIDEQ EQU   49 .               SEARCH ID EQUAL
SRCHIDHI EQU   X'51' .            SEARCH COUNT/ID HIGH
SRCHKEEQ EQU   41 .               SEARCH KEY EQUAL
TIC      EQU   8 .                TRANSFER IN CHANNEL
READC    EQU   18 .               READ COUNT
ERASE    EQU   X'11' .            ERASE TO END OF TRACK
*
* USER PARAMETER AND COMPLETION BITS (AFPARFS BITS).
*
AFIOERR  EQU   B'11000000' .      ACTIVE FILE I/O ERROR
AFXCPTN  EQU   B'01000000' .      ACTIVE FILE EXCEPTION CONDITION
MACOMP2  EQU   B'00100000' .      REENTRY MACRO INTERPRETER
MACOMP1  EQU   B'00010000' .      PROCEDE TO NEXT SEGMENT
BYRECNUM EQU   B'10000000' .      SEARCH BY RECORD NUMBER
LAST     EQU   B'01000000' .      POSITIONED TO LAST RECORD OF FILE
NEXT     EQU   B'01000000' .      PROCESS NEXT RECORD
HIGHEQ   EQU   B'01000000' .      KEY REQUESTED IS HIGH OR EQUAL
MULTIPLE EQU   B'00100000' .      PROCESS MULTIPLE RECORDS
REPOST2  EQU   B'00100000' .      POSITION IS AFTER LAST RECORD OF SEG.
GLOBAL   EQU   B'00010000' .      REQUEST IS FOR GLOBAL FILE
REPOST1  EQU   B'00010000' .      POSITION IS BETWEEN FIRST AND LSST
XLOOSIV  EQU   B'00001000' .      EXCLUSIVE CONTROL FOR GLOBAL FILES
READREC  EQU   B'00000100' .      READ REFERENCED RECORD
READKEY  EQU   B'00000010' .      READ REFERENCED KEY
BEFORE   EQU   B'00000001' .      FINAL POSITION IS BEFORE LAST PROCESS
OLDFILE  EQU   B'00000001' .      CREATE MACRO OPTION
*
         MEND
